  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Demonstration of local coffee roasting Rwanda</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Giesen Coffee Roasters B.V. develops innovative machines and associated equipment for small to medium-sized coffee roasters. The machines can roast green coffee beans in batches from 1 to 120 kg. A specific flavour can be extracted from the beans by controlling the temperature. The machines/roasters are purchased worldwide by shops, coffee shops and coffee roasters.Giessen wants to increase its export opportunities in Rwanda by means of a demonstration project. Coffee cultivation is a crucial part of the economy there, but coffee roasting is not. Currently only a small part of the total coffee production in Rwanda is roasted. More than 90% is exported as raw green bean to large buyers abroad. These buyers often have good long-term contacts. Giessen initially focuses on the niche target group of relatively small coffee producers and cooperatives and local coffee roasters that supply the local market.A roasted bean yields much more and has a more stable price, which will also improve the position of this target group. The intended result is that farmers earn more in a sustainable manner and that a new sales market will arise for Giessen.</narrative>
  </description>
